<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1451,1166,1301]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
An Afro-American species and the most common representative of the genus in tropical America, ranging from 
<collectingCountry box="[136,195,1238,1264]" name="Cuba" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[247,356,1238,1264]" name="Honduras" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Honduras</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[389,471,1238,1264]" name="Bolivia" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and SE 
<collectingCountry box="[561,632,1238,1264]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, apparently rare in Africa, from where it is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1350,1238,1264]" name="Tanzania" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1359,1447,1238,1264]" name="Malawi" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Malawi</collectingCountry>
, 
